Service was a bit slow and lacking. Food was on the same caliber.  We stopped by on a rainy Friday evening. The restaurant was fairly slow as most tables were unoccupied. It is a wonder why (and how) it took so long to be greeted, offered drinks, and all the other steps of service. We ordered a bunch: fried chicken wings and meatballs to start, then lamb chops, filet--both medium rare, fries, brussel sprouts.  Blue Ribbon's fried chicken deserves 5 stars, always. The filet and lamb chops were disappointing. Both were overcooked, the filet was tough. We ended up ordering another order of wings when walked over to Temple Court for a proper dinner.

The ribs appetizer special was amazing. They were the best ribs I have ever had. They were smokey with the perfect balance of sweet and tangy, holding together with a char crust and yet fall off the bone tender.  The halibut was cooked to perfection, and the tandori cauliflower was perfectly roasted, encrusted with a mild but adequately spiced curry/ garam masala crust.  The spatzle with cheese was surprisingly bland despite salting, but the texture was perfect.  The bar tender was very hospitable and clearly enjoyed his job, engaging, jovial yet reserved.

My favorite FiDi restaurant for brunch and hosting special events.  Special Events: The venue for my sister's bridal shower cancelled the morning of the event, and I called Blue Ribbon Federal Grill in a complete panic. Sam, the manager, was calm and reassuring on the phone and said he could take care of the situation, no problem. He was able to put aside tables for 30 people, and allowed me to bring my own cake and balloons and use the space for over 3 hours. The food and drinks were wonderful, and my guests had a wonderful time. This restaurant really saved the day, and I'll be forever grateful. Their service is incredible!  Brunch: Like I said, it's my favorite FiDi brunch spot. My favorites are the Smoked Salmon Benedict (delicate, flavorful, plated very well) and the Chorizo Hash (an American, let's-get-full, savory delight). It's a nice quiet spot to enjoy a late morning and have a real conversation with your party.  Dinner: Had a great Sunday birthday dinner here with my parents. Very clean and new and sharp - the staff was professional, nice, and knowledgeable. Appetizers, like the veal tartare and tuna poke, we're delicious. Extensive alcohol selection.

Update: So I went for lunch today and I must say that all the issues I had with the place the first time I went were COMPLETELY ironed out. First off, the service was impeccable. We mustve been asked at least 5x how everything was going. The lunch menu was delicious with a special award going to the bone marrow and oxtail appetizer. Truly an amazing dish. Drinks were expertly made and again the service was top notch. I will most definitely be back again.  Went for a breakfast meeting at the new AKA Hotel downtown.  The service seemed unrefined. Waiters asking for orders twice, not delivering the right food to the right seat, etc.. The food however was good. The lox was fresh, the ham quiche was made well and the bacon and potato sides were good. However I don't think I would return only because there are better places in the area.

In short, you'll find good food, as well as subpar and (unintentionally) rude service. The number of times our table was interrupted was truly unparalleled. Forgot to mention specials; reaching across our faces to refill water without asking (4 or 5 times); sommeliers; forgot to ask about how the dish should be cooked; asking how the experience was; asking how the experience was again. And we were only there for an hour. To be clear, no one was intentionally rude. The servers and host were gracious--but they were also seemingly poorly trained.
